signoz:index/logPipeline:LogPipeline.description:
The SigNoz log-processing pipeline set. SigNoz manages log pipelines as a single versioned, ordered collection, so this is a **singleton** resource — declare at most one. Applying publishes a new pipeline-set version; destroying publishes an empty set.

## Example Usage

<!--Start PulumiCodeChooser -->
```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as signoz from "@jooon/pulumi-signoz";

// Singleton: declare at most one signoz_log_pipeline per SigNoz instance.
// Applying publishes a new pipeline-set version; destroying clears the set.
const main = new signoz.LogPipeline("main", {pipelines: JSON.stringify([{
    orderId: 1,
    name: "drop-health-checks",
    alias: "drop-health-checks",
    enabled: true,
    filter: {
        op: "AND",
        items: [{
            key: {
                key: "http.target",
            },
            op: "=",
            value: "/healthz",
        }],
    },
    config: [],
}])});
```
